haviour: Unprovoked attack, unusual behaviour (aggressive, salivating, wild appearing tame, uncoordinated movements) | Category of Exposure | Category 1 (Touching/feeding animal, licking of intact skin): No action if history of vaccination reliable. If history not reliable, manage as category 2 | Category 2 (Nibbling of uncovered skin, superficial scratch NO SKIN BREACH NO BLEEDING): Wound management + Rabies vaccine full course + Rabies immunoglobulin if immune-compromised | Category 3 (Bites or scratches that penetrate skin, licking of mucous membranes, ANY contact with a bat): Wound management + Rabies vaccine full course + Rabies immunoglobulin | RIG is CRITICAL in head/neck/face wounds - short incubation period | Wound Management: Flush well with soap and water | Clean with 0.05% chlorhexidine or 10% iodine | Avoid suturing and local anaesthetic agents | Antibiotics if indicated | Tetanus toxoid booster (TIG if severe wounds) | Rabies Vaccine (Verorab): 1 Amp/dose for adults and children | Schedule: Day 0, 3, 7, and 14 | Route: IMI deltoid or anterolateral thigh (avoid gluteus maximus) | If dose delayed, resume and complete regimen, do not restart | SAFE in lactation and pregnancy, same dose | Human Rabies Immunoglobulin (Human Rabigam): Dose 20 IU/kg | Infiltrate entire dose around/into wound | Dilute with saline if more volume needed for multiple wounds | Can be given up to 7 days post vaccine administration, give ASAP | Equine Rabies Immunoglobulin (Equirab): Dose 40 IU/kg | 1:150,000 risk of anaphylaxis | Administer in setting with resuscitation equipment available | Human Rabigam dosing table: 5kg=100 units/0.7ml, 10kg=200/1.3ml, 15kg=300/2.0ml, 20kg=400/2.7ml, 25kg=500/3.3ml, 30kg=600/4.0ml, 40kg=800/5.3ml, 50kg=1000/6.7ml, 60kg=1200/8.0ml, 70kg=1400/9.3ml, 80kg=1600/10.7ml, 90kg=1800/12.0ml, 100kg=2000/13.3ml | Equine Equirab dosing table: 5kg=200/1ml, 10kg=400/2ml, 15kg=600/3ml, 20kg=800/4ml, 25kg=1000/5ml, 30kg=1200/6ml, 40kg=1600/8ml, 50kg=2000/10ml, 60kg=2400/12ml, 70kg=2800/14ml, 80kg=3200/16ml, 90kg=3600/18ml, 100kg=4000/20ml | NICD 24-hour clinician hotline: 0800 212 552 | HJH ID Consultants | Source: NICD Rabies Guidelines 2021